post_text:
#NEWS: Little Lake CSD Parents! Enrollment is now open!

We are offering the choice between Hybrid Learning or the Virtual Academy for the 2020-2021 School Year. The Hybrid Learning Model will feature 2 days of in-class instruction and 3 days of distance learning for grades 1-8, and an AM or PM schedule for TK & Kindergarten students with a full day of Distance Learning on Fridays. The Virtual Learning Academy will consist of full-time distance learning with daily virtual interactions with LLCSD teachers.

The deadline to register and make a selection is Tuesday, July 21! Visit https://www.llcsd.net/ to enroll today!
.
.

#NEWS: Due to the recommendation made by Los Angeles County Office of Education (LACOE), Little Lake City School District will be dismissing students from school beginning Monday, March 16th and continuing until Friday, April 3rd. No students will be attending school during this time.

As new information becomes available to the district we will be sure to communicate it to the community via social media platforms, email and the district website (www.llcsd.net). We thank you for your patience and understanding as the district continues to work continues to work with LACOE and the Los Angeles County Department of Public Health to ensure the health and safety of our students and staff. Further updates will be provided via email.

If you have any questions please contact the district office at (562) 868-8241.
.
.
#LittleLakeCSD

#NEWS: We‚Äôre proud to announce that Lake Center Middle School has been named an Honor Roll School by Educational Results Partnership!

ERP is a data science organization that recognizes schools with high performance in Math and Science. Sponsored by the Campaign for Business and Education Excellence, the ERP Honor Roll is the only school recognition program in the state that uses student achievement outcome data, and is a valuable resource for all schools to identify successful peers and learn about best practices that improve student success.

Thank you to our teachers, staff, and parents for supporting our students at Lake Center! This recognition would not have been possible without you.
.
.
